content: In the year 2030, people do not own anything. This means that they do not own cars, houses, appliances, or clothes. Instead, they have access to transportation, accommodation, food, and other things they need in their daily lives. These things are free, so people do not need to buy them. However, this also means that people have no privacy, as they do not own anything. Despite this, life is still better than it has ever been.
